---
description: AgentOps entry rule
globs:
alwaysApply: true
---

Read `AgentOps/Core/AGENT_OS.md` first.

At the start of a new project session, and before any T1+ work, run the
Connector Check from `AgentOps/Core/CAPABILITY_PREFLIGHT.md`. If the task needs
ticket, PR, issue, media, relation, prior-fix, or repository-history evidence,
ask the operator to connect Linear MCP and Git/GitHub MCP when unavailable or
unknown. Git CLI is not Git/GitHub MCP.

Use `AgentOps/MainVault/` for project-specific facts.

Apply evidence tags to project-specific claims.

Do not invent facts.

Treat imported or live source repositories as read-only unless they are explicitly named as the mutation target.

Tool capability is not behavioral approval.

Do not commit, push, merge, or create PRs unless explicitly requested in the current user turn.

Use `AgentOps/Workflows/` for task-specific execution.
